node.text: with @kit.griffiths and @alannah.carr . After a great day on the boat with @graceshorevillas , we slowly made our way back and saw a couple dolphins breach. I masked up, grabbed my @gopro and hopped in. This first clip is the moment I was underwater looking for the dolphins and they appeared in the distance. They swam right by, looked right at me, and turned around to come play. From that moment we played with them for about 20 minutes until the mom decided it was time to go and moved Dreamer along with her tail fin against its dorsal fin keeping her moving along not to get distracted by playing again.  Here’s a condensed version of our 20 minute interaction with these amazing creatures. I was blown away by the interaction and communication. I grew up around dolphins in coastal GA but never seen wild dolphins interact with humans in this way. There was clearly mutual communication and interaction going on here, and truly made me realize how these animals are the closest living things to humans in the ocean. #dolphin #dolphins #marinelife #turksandcaicos #tci #ocean #nature #wildlife #islandvibes #paradise

node.text: Hope you’re not tired of wave pool clips because I have a couple more coming. I was gonna save this for #failfriday but I took a heavy slam today that I’ll be sharing tomorrow instead. This was my first wave on “barrel mode” on my skimboard at @alaia.bay .  Captured by @jakelamons 📷 || #skimboarding #surfing #wavepool
